From b1a5dca08a662ab1339841f268627d3cd9a075f7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ganesh Kariganuru Mahabalesh <gkarigan@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 2 Sep 2025 14:01:58 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] QSDK:CP:wifi:ath12k: Ensure arvif is created before updating
 the PPE VP table

Currently, in ath12k_ppe_ds_attach_vlan_vif_link(), the function iterates
over all links in the parent vif and attempts to update PPE VP table for 
each associated arvif. However, the current implementation only checks
for null arvif pointers and does not verify whether the arvif has been 
fully created.

Fix this by adding a check for arvif->is_created before proceeding for
PPE VP table updation.

Patch-dependency:
	0337-10-QSDK-DP-wifi-Enable-DS-support-for-WDS-AP_VLAN-inter.patch

Signed-off-by: Ganesh Kariganuru Mahabalesh <gkarigan@qti.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/ppe.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/ppe.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/ppe.c
@@ -999,7 +999,7 @@ void ath12k_ppe_ds_attach_vlan_vif_link(
 	for_each_set_bit(link_id, &links_map, IEEE80211_MLD_MAX_NUM_LINKS) {
 		ap_arvif = rcu_dereference(ap_ahvif->link[link_id]);
 
-		if (!ap_arvif)
+		if (!ap_arvif || !ap_arvif->is_created)
 			continue;
 
 		ar = ap_arvif->ar;
